The evidence with the title 'Section 2: opinions of gun owners, non-gun owners | pew ... ' says Mar 12, 2013  ... A majority (55%) say that stricter gun laws would make it more difficult for people to protect their homes and families.  ... Yet people in NRA households overwhelmingly favor making private gun sales and sales at gun shows subject to background checks: 74% favor this proposal while just 26% are opposed. 
